    10	
    11	Moderator's note: The following article is a lengthy excerpt from a
    12	recent issue of FIDONEWS concerning individual privacy and the use of
    13	aliases or handles in computer-based communications.  It was submitted by
    14	a comp.society reader who used a handle; because the excerpt is a cross-
    15	post from another electronic publication, I have taken the liberty of
    16	viewing the use of a handle by sender as a request for privacy and
    17	anonymity similar to the request a newspaper editor might receive in a
    18	letter to the editor.  Thus, while reprinting the submission, the name
    19	and address of the sender are "withheld upon request."  The article
    20	raises a number of good points; the submission by a reader using a handle
    21	to preserve anonymity makes a point; and the editorial action of
    22	submitting the reader's posting anonymously makes the question current.
    23	What are the implications of using aliases on the net?
    24	
    25	Greg Welsh, moderator, comp.society
    26	Internet:  Socicom@american.edu
    27	Bitnet:    Socicom@auvm.bitnet
