    81	
    82	
    83	We should never so entirely avoid danger as to appear
    84	irresolute and cowardly.  But, at the same time, we should
    85	avoid unnecessarily exposing ourselves to danger, than
    86	which nothing can be more foolish.  [Cicero]
    87	
